Design Pattern in Android (Kotlin)

A Pattern which provides reusability of code.

Most Common used pattern in Android
1. Creational pattern : Creational pattern used for creating objects without
showing How they created.
Examples - Builder, Singleton, Dependency injection, Factory

2. Structural pattern : Structural pattern used for structure class. A structured
class is easy to understand and easy to read.
Examples - Adapter, Facade (Decorator, Composite (Mostly not used))

3. Behavioral pattern : In Behavioral pattern, we don't know how data
will behave in future. We don't know, Which class/Object will responsible for
doing something in future.
Examples - Listeners, LiveData, Observer, RxAndroid



